    <h1 class="heading1">IVF and Fertility Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our IVF and Fertility Department offers advanced reproductive technologies and compassionate care to individuals and couples struggling with infertility. Led by a team of experienced fertility specialists, embryologists, and reproductive endocrinologists, we provide personalized treatment plans and support services to help our patients achieve their dream of parenthood.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Infertility Evaluation</h4>
            <p>We offer comprehensive infertility evaluations to identify the underlying causes of infertility and develop personalized treatment plans. Our fertility specialists conduct thorough assessments, including medical history reviews, physical exams, hormone testing, ovarian reserve testing, semen analysis, and imaging studies, to diagnose infertility factors and determine the most appropriate treatment options.</p>

            <h4>In Vitro Fertilization (IVF)</h4>
            <p>Our IVF program provides state-of-the-art reproductive technologies to help individuals and couples overcome infertility challenges. We offer a full range of IVF services, including ovarian stimulation, egg retrieval, sperm retrieval, fertilization, embryo culture, embryo transfer, and cryopreservation (embryo freezing and storage), utilizing advanced laboratory techniques and equipment to maximize success rates.</p>

            <h4>Assisted Reproductive Technologies (ART)</h4>
            <p>In addition to IVF, we offer various assisted reproductive technologies (ART) to enhance fertility and improve pregnancy outcomes. These may include intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI), preimplantation genetic testing (PGT), assisted hatching, embryo biopsy, and embryo selection techniques, tailored to meet the specific needs of our patients.</p>

            <h4>Fertility Preservation</h4>
            <p>For individuals facing fertility-threatening conditions or undergoing medical treatments that may affect fertility, such as cancer treatments or surgery, we offer fertility preservation options. Our fertility specialists provide counseling and services for egg freezing (oocyte cryopreservation), sperm banking, and embryo freezing, allowing patients to preserve their fertility for future family-building efforts.</p>

            <h4>Donor Egg and Sperm Programs</h4>
            <p>For individuals and couples experiencing challenges with egg or sperm quality, we offer donor egg and sperm programs to expand their options for conception. Our IVF and Fertility Department coordinates donor matching, screening, and treatment cycles, ensuring that patients receive high-quality donor gametes and comprehensive support throughout the process.</p>

            <h4>Fertility Counseling and Support</h4>
            <p>We understand that struggling with infertility can be emotionally challenging. Our IVF and Fertility Department provides fertility counseling, support groups, and resources to help patients cope with the emotional, psychological, and social aspects of infertility. We offer compassionate guidance, education, and coping strategies to empower patients on their fertility journey.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
